Because $\bar{A}'_{\mathbf{w}_1}$ contains the empty set term, it is strictly positive. We can therefore divide both sides by $\bar{A}'_{\mathbf{w}_1}$ to obtain
\begin{equation*}
    1 \ge \frac{K^2}{d_3^2}, 
\end{equation*}
which implies $d_3 \ge K$ and the proof is finished.
\end{proof}

